Nigerian singer and songwriter, Ayoleyi Hanniel Solomon, better known as Reekado Banks is currently stranded in another African country, Gabon, urging the federal government to open borders, so he can return home.
The 26-year-old musician cannot return to his home country, Nigeria due to strict restrictions following the coronavirus pandemic.
Reekado posted a picture of himself on his verified Instagram page where he wrote; ”Smiling like everything is okay but deep down Gabon ti su mi(I am tired of Gabon). E ba mi shi border ejo (please open the border)”.

 

			
